================================
=== OJS Web Feeds Plugin
=== Version: 1.1
=== Release date: May 30, 2006
=== Author: Alf Eaton <alf@hubmed.org>
=== Contribution: Juan Alperin <juan@geeky.net>
================================

About
-----
This plugin for OJS 2 provides a set of syndication feeds for the current issue in RSS1.0/RDF and Atom formats.  Feed links are embedded into the HTML header for the current issue and are available to all RSS/Atom-aware browsers and aggregators as per standard web specifications.

License
-------
This plugin is licensed under the GNU General Public License v2. See the file COPYING for the complete terms of this license.

System Requirements
-------------------
Same requirements as the OJS 2.1.x core.

Installation
------------
To install the plugin:
 - copy the webFeed folder into OJS/plugins/generic
 - enable the plugin by going to:  Home > User > Journal Management > Plugin Management  and selecting "ENABLE" under "Feed Plugin"


Known Issues/Limitations
---------
- the plugin does not currently support the RSS2.0 feed format.

Localization
------------
Currently in en_US (U.S. English) and es_ES (Espaol Espaa) locales

